1. Compile the programme for the simulation of motifs

  $ gcc -o motif_sim motif_sim.c

2. Uncompress the basic input dataset

  $ bunzip2 hsapiens.1200_genes.fa.bz2

3. Generate the motifs and the modified input dataset <8, 1, 2, 1>, using the basic input dataset

  $ ./motif_sim hsapiens.1200_genes.fa 8 1 2 1 100 hsapiens.1200_genes_mod.fa motifs.txt

4. Go up one directory

  $ cd ..

5. Compile MoTeX

  $ make -f Makefile.OMP.gcc

6. Run MoTeX with <int> threads --- it requires around ten minutes with 48 threads

  $ ./motexOMP -a DNA -i ./data/hsapiens.1200_genes_mod.fa -o output.motex -d 0 -k 8 -e 2 -q 1 -t <int>

7. Change to directory `data'

  $ cd data

8. Compile the programme for the accuracy of MoTeX

  $ gcc -o motex_acc motex_acc.c

9. Check the accuracy of MoTeX using the motifs and the output of MoTeX

  $ ./motex_acc motifs.txt ../output.motex
